'''AT''' or '''AT(AT)''' is an [[Elvish]] [[Sundocarme|root]] signifying "back, again". '''AT(A)''' signifies "re-".<ref name=Elda>{{PE|Eldarin}}, p. 148</ref><ref name=Ety349>{{LR|Etymologies}}, p. 349</ref>

==Derivatives==

*[[Quenya]]: ''[[ata]]'' ("again"); ''[[at-]]'' ("back, again, re-")<ref name=Ety349/>
*[[Noldorin]] ([[Sindarin]]): ''[[ad-]]''<ref name=Ety349/><ref>{{VT|45a}}, p. 6</ref>

*Root [[AT-TA]] ("[number] 2")<ref name=Elda/>
